<font color="#FF0000">ADDING MY VOICE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Mar 29 23:58:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well, PBS, it seems like you hit a raw nerve. Chet's comments are descriptive of the feelings of many. <br><br>
1. This is the only site anywhere that encourages a true dialog with everyone. Other sites have a gung ho military mentality that inhibits the unfettered freedom of expression this forum permits.<br><br>
2. This dialog is the first time for many Vietnam Veterans to openly discuss thier feelings and concerns, and have them actually appreciated, discussed, debated, and, in some cases, resolved. There is real human drama here, often far better than anything Shakespeare created.<br><br>
3. Many Vietnam Veterans began here to recover self esteem, that poorly understood fragile commodity of life most take for granted, unless you happen to be missing some. The effects of the Vietnam War have an almost surreal capacity to dissolve self esteem, as many of us are acutely aware.<br><br>
4. Many other people will loose as well. As I have stated elsewhere, this site is a unique opportunity for PBS to experience its true manifest destiny and provide for real public education on the Vietnam War. It must not be forgotten that most of us here have lived this history. There is no better opportunity to truly understand than here with us.<br><br>
We live in a throw-away society. It is natural for many of us to interpret the possible closing of this dialog as just another bleak conclusion of what might have been a brighter episode in the lives of disposable Vietnam Veterans. That's another story.<br><br>
Some of us who can afford it financially contribute to PBS. Our unfettered contributions here, however, far outweigh anything of financial value. In the final analysis, we truly gave of ourselves, and we didn't expect any coffee mugs, umbrellas, or platinum patron awards, either. Most of us will continue to feel pretty damn good about that for a long time to come!<br><br>
Again, I add my voice with those who do not wish to see this dialog closed. 
